headline: Goldman Sachs (GS): Assessing Valuation After a 61% One-Year Share Price Surge
summary: Goldman Sachs Group (GS) keeps grinding higher, with the stock up roughly 7% over the past month and about 61% over the past year, as investors lean into its steady earnings recovery. See our latest analysis for Goldman Sachs Group. That strength reflects more than just a good month, with a 30 day share price return of about 7% building on a powerful 12 month total shareholder return of roughly 61% as markets re rate GS earnings power.
